WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.988 align:middle line:90%


00:00:00.988 --> 00:00:03.952 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:03.952 --> 00:00:46.010 align:middle line:90%


00:00:46.010 --> 00:00:47.580 align:middle line:84%
>>The Order of the
Temple of Solomon

00:00:47.580 --> 00:00:51.160 align:middle line:84%
had been founded in the
aftermath of the First Crusade,

00:00:51.160 --> 00:00:52.970 align:middle line:84%
a Christian military
expedition which

00:00:52.970 --> 00:00:55.212 align:middle line:84%
had captured Jerusalem
from the Muslims.

00:00:55.212 --> 00:01:01.400 align:middle line:90%


00:01:01.400 --> 00:01:04.239 align:middle line:84%
The first Templars had
dedicated their lives to God

00:01:04.239 --> 00:01:06.480 align:middle line:84%
by protecting
pilgrims, but the Order

00:01:06.480 --> 00:01:09.800 align:middle line:84%
had soon proved itself to be
the most effective military unit

00:01:09.800 --> 00:01:10.850 align:middle line:90%
in the crusading army.

00:01:10.850 --> 00:01:17.794 align:middle line:90%


00:01:17.794 --> 00:01:20.274 align:middle line:90%
[BATTLE SOUNDS]

00:01:20.274 --> 00:01:23.746 align:middle line:90%


00:01:23.746 --> 00:01:26.420 align:middle line:84%
At the Horns of Hattin,
the Templar knights

00:01:26.420 --> 00:01:29.615 align:middle line:84%
had been singled out by
Saladin and almost eliminated

00:01:29.615 --> 00:01:30.890 align:middle line:90%
from the Holy Land.

00:01:30.890 --> 00:01:34.110 align:middle line:90%


00:01:34.110 --> 00:01:36.700 align:middle line:84%
But in their short
60-year existence,

00:01:36.700 --> 00:01:39.850 align:middle line:84%
the Templars had constructed
an enormous support network

00:01:39.850 --> 00:01:42.795 align:middle line:84%
throughout Western Europe
that provided the front line

00:01:42.795 --> 00:01:44.850 align:middle line:90%
with men and supplies.

00:01:44.850 --> 00:01:47.830 align:middle line:84%
In fact, this
elite military unit

00:01:47.830 --> 00:01:50.230 align:middle line:84%
had created for
itself the world's

00:01:50.230 --> 00:01:52.105 align:middle line:90%
first multinational corporation.

00:01:52.105 --> 00:02:10.669 align:middle line:90%


00:02:10.669 --> 00:02:12.790 align:middle line:84%
Since the Order of
the Temple had first

00:02:12.790 --> 00:02:15.310 align:middle line:84%
been established early
in the 12th century,

00:02:15.310 --> 00:02:18.590 align:middle line:84%
it had set out to attract
recruits and raise funds.

00:02:18.590 --> 00:02:21.080 align:middle line:84%
Although an individual
knight could own nothing,

00:02:21.080 --> 00:02:23.305 align:middle line:84%
he still needed horses,
weaponry, and servants

00:02:23.305 --> 00:02:25.770 align:middle line:84%
if he was to carry out
God's work effectively.

00:02:25.770 --> 00:02:31.020 align:middle line:90%


00:02:31.020 --> 00:02:34.920 align:middle line:84%
The king of Jerusalem had
initially aided the Templars.

00:02:34.920 --> 00:02:36.730 align:middle line:84%
Among the many
reasons for doing so

00:02:36.730 --> 00:02:40.140 align:middle line:84%
was the knowledge that visiting
pilgrims brought much needed

00:02:40.140 --> 00:02:41.970 align:middle line:84%
income to the fledgling
Crusader states.

00:02:41.970 --> 00:02:43.340 align:middle line:90%


00:02:43.340 --> 00:02:47.772 align:middle line:84%
Pilgrims required food and
lodging, they paid road tolls,

00:02:47.772 --> 00:02:48.730 align:middle line:90%
and they brought gifts.

00:02:48.730 --> 00:02:52.830 align:middle line:90%


00:02:52.830 --> 00:02:54.410 align:middle line:84%
From the very
beginning, the Templars

00:02:54.410 --> 00:02:57.570 align:middle line:84%
were entirely comfortable
with the economic realities

00:02:57.570 --> 00:03:00.074 align:middle line:90%
of serving God in the Holy Land.

00:03:00.074 --> 00:03:20.780 align:middle line:90%


00:03:20.780 --> 00:03:23.390 align:middle line:84%
The Templar
corporation, or network,

00:03:23.390 --> 00:03:25.530 align:middle line:84%
began in Western
Europe, built up

00:03:25.530 --> 00:03:28.290 align:middle line:84%
from gifts of land donated
by men and women who

00:03:28.290 --> 00:03:31.160 align:middle line:84%
wanted to protect their
immortal souls by supporting

00:03:31.160 --> 00:03:32.683 align:middle line:90%
the Crusaders in the Holy Land.

00:03:32.683 --> 00:03:37.620 align:middle line:90%


00:03:37.620 --> 00:03:40.870 align:middle line:84%
Many of the earliest donations
received by the Templars

00:03:40.870 --> 00:03:43.180 align:middle line:84%
were from men who wanted to
join the Order themselves.

00:03:43.180 --> 00:03:47.410 align:middle line:90%


00:03:47.410 --> 00:03:49.130 align:middle line:84%
One of the most
substantial donors

00:03:49.130 --> 00:03:51.613 align:middle line:84%
came from Champagne
in Northern France.

00:03:51.613 --> 00:03:57.390 align:middle line:90%


00:03:57.390 --> 00:04:00.750 align:middle line:84%
>>Hugh Count of Champagne
joined the Order in the 1120s.

00:04:00.750 --> 00:04:04.730 align:middle line:10%
And he was one of its
earliest important patrons.

00:04:04.730 --> 00:04:08.760 align:middle line:84%
But once he joined the
Order, he lost the status

00:04:08.760 --> 00:04:11.800 align:middle line:84%
that came with being an
important territorial ruler.

00:04:11.800 --> 00:04:16.490 align:middle line:84%
He had to abrogate his own
will to that of the Master.

00:04:16.490 --> 00:04:19.790 align:middle line:84%
And he had to live the
life of an ordinary knight.

00:04:19.790 --> 00:04:23.630 align:middle line:84%
So one gave up a considerable
amount, in terms of status

00:04:23.630 --> 00:04:26.890 align:middle line:84%
and in material comfort, in
order to become a Templar.

00:04:26.890 --> 00:04:30.920 align:middle line:84%
But if you sincerely believe
that what really matters

00:04:30.920 --> 00:04:34.170 align:middle line:84%
is your immortal soul, and not
your short and transitory life

00:04:34.170 --> 00:04:37.150 align:middle line:84%
on earth, then it would
be seen as worth it.

00:04:37.150 --> 00:04:40.780 align:middle line:90%


00:04:40.780 --> 00:04:43.900 align:middle line:84%
>>The Templars gratefully
accepted many such gifts

00:04:43.900 --> 00:04:46.790 align:middle line:84%
of land, which were channelled
into productive communities

00:04:46.790 --> 00:04:48.870 align:middle line:84%
where the brothers in the
West lived and worked.

00:04:48.870 --> 00:04:50.520 align:middle line:90%


00:04:50.520 --> 00:04:53.540 align:middle line:84%
It was these communities,
called preceptories,

00:04:53.540 --> 00:04:55.600 align:middle line:84%
that became the bedrock
of the Templar network.

00:04:55.600 --> 00:05:01.830 align:middle line:90%


00:05:01.830 --> 00:05:05.440 align:middle line:84%
>>I think that the Templars
gave a good deal of thought

00:05:05.440 --> 00:05:10.330 align:middle line:84%
to the best way of exploiting
their Western preceptories

00:05:10.330 --> 00:05:15.850 align:middle line:84%
for the purposes of supporting
their military front line.

00:05:15.850 --> 00:05:19.640 align:middle line:84%
But it's not entirely easy
to do this consistently,

00:05:19.640 --> 00:05:23.586 align:middle line:84%
since by their very nature,
donations tend to be random.

00:05:23.586 --> 00:05:25.810 align:middle line:84%
As time went on,
they tried quite

00:05:25.810 --> 00:05:28.910 align:middle line:84%
hard to rationalize
their holdings

00:05:28.910 --> 00:05:32.300 align:middle line:84%
in a way which would
make them more effective.

00:05:32.300 --> 00:05:35.260 align:middle line:84%
And even, in some
areas, to provide

00:05:35.260 --> 00:05:39.426 align:middle line:84%
preceptories which were rather
specialist-- perhaps specialist

00:05:39.426 --> 00:05:43.990 align:middle line:84%
in banking or in stud
farms or in providing

00:05:43.990 --> 00:05:45.995 align:middle line:90%
shipping and so on.

00:05:45.995 --> 00:05:50.190 align:middle line:90%


00:05:50.190 --> 00:05:54.030 align:middle line:84%
>>A typical rural preceptory of
the Templars usually comprised

00:05:54.030 --> 00:05:56.850 align:middle line:84%
of farmland centered
around to manor house,

00:05:56.850 --> 00:05:59.960 align:middle line:84%
with any numbers of barns,
stables, and outhouses

00:05:59.960 --> 00:06:02.080 align:middle line:84%
depending on the size
and location of the farm.

00:06:02.080 --> 00:06:08.140 align:middle line:90%


00:06:08.140 --> 00:06:11.080 align:middle line:84%
No entire preceptories
remain today,

00:06:11.080 --> 00:06:13.970 align:middle line:84%
but many individual
buildings do.

00:06:13.970 --> 00:06:16.790 align:middle line:84%
These enormous barns were
constructed by the Knights

00:06:16.790 --> 00:06:19.110 align:middle line:90%
Templar more than 800 years ago.

00:06:19.110 --> 00:06:23.440 align:middle line:90%


00:06:23.440 --> 00:06:26.950 align:middle line:84%
The aim of all Templar
preceptories was to make money.

00:06:26.950 --> 00:06:30.490 align:middle line:84%
A third of all income went to
the knights on the frontier.

00:06:30.490 --> 00:06:33.030 align:middle line:84%
Every donation, large
or small, was fully

00:06:33.030 --> 00:06:34.920 align:middle line:90%
exploited for maximum revenue.

00:06:34.920 --> 00:06:36.100 align:middle line:90%


00:06:36.100 --> 00:06:38.480 align:middle line:84%
If they were given
unused land, they

00:06:38.480 --> 00:06:40.170 align:middle line:90%
had it settled and cultivated.

00:06:40.170 --> 00:06:41.220 align:middle line:90%


00:06:41.220 --> 00:06:43.580 align:middle line:84%
New mills, wine
presses, and ovens

00:06:43.580 --> 00:06:47.185 align:middle line:84%
were constructed to soak up
the extra agricultural produce.

00:06:47.185 --> 00:06:49.400 align:middle line:90%


00:06:49.400 --> 00:06:51.585 align:middle line:84%
And new village and town
markets were created.

00:06:51.585 --> 00:06:54.060 align:middle line:90%


00:06:54.060 --> 00:06:56.990 align:middle line:84%
In this way, the economy
of an entire region

00:06:56.990 --> 00:06:58.295 align:middle line:90%
could steadily be boosted.

00:06:58.295 --> 00:07:00.620 align:middle line:90%


00:07:00.620 --> 00:07:02.750 align:middle line:84%
But it also meant
that the Templars

00:07:02.750 --> 00:07:05.920 align:middle line:84%
could take economic
control of whole areas

00:07:05.920 --> 00:07:08.158 align:middle line:84%
as they bought up
businesses and land.

00:07:08.158 --> 00:07:11.030 align:middle line:90%


00:07:11.030 --> 00:07:14.910 align:middle line:84%
In the Champagne town of
Prova, the Knights Templar

00:07:14.910 --> 00:07:17.340 align:middle line:84%
would eventually own
more than 70 properties.

00:07:17.340 --> 00:07:20.540 align:middle line:90%


00:07:20.540 --> 00:07:22.730 align:middle line:84%
The Templars were always
improving their market

00:07:22.730 --> 00:07:24.870 align:middle line:84%
position, and their
dominance always

00:07:24.870 --> 00:07:27.710 align:middle line:84%
caused considerable resentment
among both peasants and land

00:07:27.710 --> 00:07:28.850 align:middle line:90%
holders.

00:07:28.850 --> 00:07:32.800 align:middle line:84%
To their rivals, the Templars
had one particularly unfair

00:07:32.800 --> 00:07:37.050 align:middle line:84%
advantage: their holdings
were exempt taxes or tithes.

00:07:37.050 --> 00:07:41.650 align:middle line:90%


00:07:41.650 --> 00:07:46.570 align:middle line:84%
>>It was normal
for the population,

00:07:46.570 --> 00:07:49.700 align:middle line:84%
in one form or
another, to pay tithes.

00:07:49.700 --> 00:07:53.020 align:middle line:84%
The Templars were granted
an exemption from tithe

00:07:53.020 --> 00:07:59.540 align:middle line:84%
on the land they acquired, which
enabled them to grow, perhaps,

00:07:59.540 --> 00:08:02.080 align:middle line:84%
more rapidly than they
would have done before.

00:08:02.080 --> 00:08:06.975 align:middle line:84%
So in that sense, they are
not paying the proportion

00:08:06.975 --> 00:08:13.160 align:middle line:84%
of their income into the
church, which you might normally

00:08:13.160 --> 00:08:14.940 align:middle line:84%
have expected them
to have to do.

00:08:14.940 --> 00:08:17.470 align:middle line:84%
Again, the justification
here is that the money

00:08:17.470 --> 00:08:19.530 align:middle line:84%
is being contributed
towards the church.

00:08:19.530 --> 00:08:21.930 align:middle line:84%
It's been contributed
towards the Holy War.

00:08:21.930 --> 00:08:24.960 align:middle line:84%
I think, inevitably, however,
when somebody gets a privilege,

00:08:24.960 --> 00:08:26.880 align:middle line:84%
somebody else
objects to the fact

00:08:26.880 --> 00:08:28.490 align:middle line:90%
that they have a privilege.

00:08:28.490 --> 00:08:35.220 align:middle line:90%


00:08:35.220 --> 00:08:37.679 align:middle line:84%
>>Within 30 years
of its foundation,

00:08:37.679 --> 00:08:40.780 align:middle line:84%
the Temple was managing
farms and urban properties

00:08:40.780 --> 00:08:43.095 align:middle line:84%
throughout France, England,
and much of Europe.

00:08:43.095 --> 00:08:44.169 align:middle line:90%


00:08:44.169 --> 00:08:46.930 align:middle line:84%
They had a European headquarters
in Paris and London.

00:08:46.930 --> 00:08:50.340 align:middle line:90%


00:08:50.340 --> 00:08:53.180 align:middle line:84%
Many of the Templar properties
on the Iberian Peninsula

00:08:53.180 --> 00:08:56.226 align:middle line:84%
were fortified, as the Muslims
retained a strong presence

00:08:56.226 --> 00:08:57.225 align:middle line:90%
on the Spanish mainland.

00:08:57.225 --> 00:09:01.780 align:middle line:90%


00:09:01.780 --> 00:09:04.570 align:middle line:84%
The Templar network provided
security and lodgings

00:09:04.570 --> 00:09:07.100 align:middle line:84%
all along the main
trade routes of Europe,

00:09:07.100 --> 00:09:08.858 align:middle line:90%
as well as to the Holy Land.

00:09:08.858 --> 00:09:13.850 align:middle line:90%


00:09:13.850 --> 00:09:15.980 align:middle line:84%
Some of their most
important offices

00:09:15.980 --> 00:09:17.770 align:middle line:84%
were at the main
Mediterranean ports.

00:09:17.770 --> 00:09:25.280 align:middle line:90%


00:09:25.280 --> 00:09:27.860 align:middle line:84%
The Temple was involved in
shipping from its earliest

00:09:27.860 --> 00:09:29.040 align:middle line:90%
days.

00:09:29.040 --> 00:09:31.290 align:middle line:84%
It had soon extended
its role from protecting

00:09:31.290 --> 00:09:33.790 align:middle line:84%
the pilgrims in the
East to protecting

00:09:33.790 --> 00:09:36.670 align:middle line:90%
pilgrims traveling to the East.

00:09:36.670 --> 00:09:39.500 align:middle line:84%
The Order constructed
an early travel agency,

00:09:39.500 --> 00:09:42.950 align:middle line:84%
providing pilgrims with not
just security, but transport

00:09:42.950 --> 00:09:43.700 align:middle line:90%
and accommodation.

00:09:43.700 --> 00:09:44.820 align:middle line:90%


00:09:44.820 --> 00:09:47.620 align:middle line:84%
At first, the Order
had chartered vessels

00:09:47.620 --> 00:09:49.720 align:middle line:84%
from the great seafaring
cities of Italy.

00:09:49.720 --> 00:09:52.300 align:middle line:84%
But once again,
the Temple decided

00:09:52.300 --> 00:09:53.960 align:middle line:90%
to improve its market position.

00:09:53.960 --> 00:10:00.530 align:middle line:90%


00:10:00.530 --> 00:10:03.100 align:middle line:10%
It built its own
ships and consolidated

00:10:03.100 --> 00:10:05.560 align:middle line:10%
its long-distance
travel business,

00:10:05.560 --> 00:10:08.250 align:middle line:10%
an industry it had helped to
create in the first place.

00:10:08.250 --> 00:10:21.150 align:middle line:90%


00:10:21.150 --> 00:10:23.840 align:middle line:84%
One of the Temple's most
important income generating

00:10:23.840 --> 00:10:27.850 align:middle line:84%
regions was on the main access
linking the great Mediterranean

00:10:27.850 --> 00:10:29.807 align:middle line:84%
and northern European
trading zones.

00:10:29.807 --> 00:10:36.020 align:middle line:90%


00:10:36.020 --> 00:10:40.420 align:middle line:84%
The Champagne region of France,
one of the Temple heartlands,

00:10:40.420 --> 00:10:43.510 align:middle line:84%
was a bridge between
north and south Europe.

00:10:43.510 --> 00:10:46.920 align:middle line:84%
It was here that enormous
trade fairs developed,

00:10:46.920 --> 00:10:49.500 align:middle line:84%
which ushered in the dawn
of international business.

00:10:49.500 --> 00:11:00.592 align:middle line:90%


00:11:00.592 --> 00:11:02.930 align:middle line:84%
The great trade
fairs of Champagne

00:11:02.930 --> 00:11:05.310 align:middle line:84%
saw the exchange of goods
from all over Europe,

00:11:05.310 --> 00:11:08.720 align:middle line:84%
which the Templars could
not fail to benefit from.

00:11:08.720 --> 00:11:12.670 align:middle line:84%
The economic boom also triggered
a financial revolution,

00:11:12.670 --> 00:11:15.570 align:middle line:84%
which saw the birth
of modern banking.

00:11:15.570 --> 00:11:18.780 align:middle line:84%
The Templars were well-placed
to enter the world of banking.

00:11:18.780 --> 00:11:20.460 align:middle line:84%
They had offices
all over Europe.

00:11:20.460 --> 00:11:23.150 align:middle line:84%
And their continuous
state of warfare

00:11:23.150 --> 00:11:25.720 align:middle line:84%
had given the Templars
the experience

00:11:25.720 --> 00:11:27.780 align:middle line:90%
of handling large sums of money.

00:11:27.780 --> 00:11:33.761 align:middle line:90%


00:11:33.761 --> 00:11:36.260 align:middle line:84%
>>One of the reasons why the
Templars were effective bankers

00:11:36.260 --> 00:11:38.460 align:middle line:90%
was that people trusted them.

00:11:38.460 --> 00:11:42.180 align:middle line:84%
And they trusted them not only
because of their integrity,

00:11:42.180 --> 00:11:44.810 align:middle line:84%
but also because they
had the physical means

00:11:44.810 --> 00:11:48.310 align:middle line:84%
to defend the money
which they held.

00:11:48.310 --> 00:11:49.680 align:middle line:90%


00:11:49.680 --> 00:11:52.300 align:middle line:84%
They had castles, and
they had armed men

00:11:52.300 --> 00:11:55.530 align:middle line:84%
who could accompany any
movement of actual specie

00:11:55.530 --> 00:11:57.595 align:middle line:90%
if that was required.

00:11:57.595 --> 00:11:58.790 align:middle line:90%


00:11:58.790 --> 00:12:01.600 align:middle line:84%
And they maintained
their reputation

00:12:01.600 --> 00:12:09.200 align:middle line:84%
for paying when required
and for honest dealing.

00:12:09.200 --> 00:12:12.026 align:middle line:84%
And in that sense,
therefore, the Templars

00:12:12.026 --> 00:12:13.150 align:middle line:90%
were successful as bankers.

00:12:13.150 --> 00:12:14.530 align:middle line:90%


00:12:14.530 --> 00:12:18.560 align:middle line:84%
The Templar Bank in Paris
performed most of the functions

00:12:18.560 --> 00:12:23.620 align:middle line:84%
that one would associate with
a modern bank, it made loans.

00:12:23.620 --> 00:12:25.450 align:middle line:90%
You could deposit money there.

00:12:25.450 --> 00:12:27.110 align:middle line:84%
It actually had
an open cash desk,

00:12:27.110 --> 00:12:30.465 align:middle line:84%
which was open many
days of the year,

00:12:30.465 --> 00:12:35.840 align:middle line:84%
particularly when it was most
needed at times when payments

00:12:35.840 --> 00:12:38.580 align:middle line:84%
were being made at the end
of the harvest and so on.

00:12:38.580 --> 00:12:40.120 align:middle line:90%


00:12:40.120 --> 00:12:42.470 align:middle line:84%
It kept separate
accounts for people.

00:12:42.470 --> 00:12:43.800 align:middle line:90%


00:12:43.800 --> 00:12:45.805 align:middle line:84%
It was involved in the
transfer of currencies.

00:12:45.805 --> 00:12:47.190 align:middle line:90%


00:12:47.190 --> 00:12:49.640 align:middle line:90%
It was involved in investment.

00:12:49.640 --> 00:12:52.950 align:middle line:84%
So most of the functions
you would associate

00:12:52.950 --> 00:12:56.840 align:middle line:84%
with a modern bank can be
seen, at least in the Templar

00:12:56.840 --> 00:12:59.010 align:middle line:84%
banks in Paris and
in London, and also

00:12:59.010 --> 00:13:01.160 align:middle line:84%
in a number of other
places, as well.

00:13:01.160 --> 00:13:03.770 align:middle line:84%
They also, perhaps,
went beyond some

00:13:03.770 --> 00:13:05.420 align:middle line:84%
of the functions
of a modern bank.

00:13:05.420 --> 00:13:08.500 align:middle line:84%
You could say that they
were performing functions

00:13:08.500 --> 00:13:11.470 align:middle line:84%
